author: itv.com
title: Commuters affected by fallen tree | Meridian
text:
Disruption on South West Trains at Ashtead due to fallen tree on the line. Wood choppers are on their way to remove the tree.
Trains to Dorking and Guildford (via Leatherhead) are affected. Until further notice lines are blocked.
There is no estimate when a normal service is likely to resume
Last updated Wed 26 Aug 2015 Travel Surrey
